\mathbb Q.
\mathbb Q(x+\langle x^2+1\rangle,-x+\langle x^2+1\rangle)\\=\mathbb Q(x+\langle x^2+1\rangle)\\=\{(a+\langle x^2+1\rangle)+(b+\langle x^2+1\rangle)(x+\langle x^2+1\rangle):a,b\in\mathbb Q\}\\=\{(a+bx)+\langle x^2+1\rangle:a,b\in\mathbb Q\}\\=\mathbb Q[x]/\langle x^2+1\rangle\text{ (due to the division algorithm)}
